A year ago, my wife began experiencing mouth ulcers, which made it difficult for her to eat spicy food and enjoy meals. Despite consulting nearly seven doctors, her condition did not improve.
Thankfully, we were referred to Dr. Srinivas a month ago. He listened to her symptoms attentively and suggested conducting a biopsy. Within three days, the results confirmed that she had Oral Lichen Planus. Dr. Srinivas prescribed a course of medication, and to our surprise, within just 25 days, her condition had reduced by 70%. Now, after consistent treatment, her condition has improved by 95%, and she can enjoy spicy food once again.
We are immensely grateful to Dr. Srinivas for his exceptional care and expertise. His treatment has significantly improved my wife's quality of life, and we highly recommend him to anyone facing similar issues.

As soon as TMJ disk displacement was diagnosed Doctor Srinivas started my treatment firstly by explaining in detail about how the disk should work normally and how my disk looks currently this gave us clear idea what was the reason for my jaw lock.  Within a month of treatment I was able to open my mouth wide and there was clear evident of progress. I'm still undergoing treatment however as per Doctor examination in follow up Visits my disk is almost in its normal position and I could feel my pain is reduced drastically and I'm able to move my jaw comfortably. I highly recommend Doctor Srinivas for treatment of TMJ related disorders.
Dr. K. Srinivas sir is very good, friendly nature, explanation of health issue is neatly and treatment is  very good.

I strongly recommend Dr. Srinivas as he is very friendly & patiently hears all queries, explains the root-cause,  diagnosis followed by treatment very clearly. I had to undergo inner cheek biopsy & there was absolutely 0-pain through out the procedure & am healing well.  All his staff members also very nice, always reachable (right from reception, assistants and dental nurses). Great experience!

I, strongly recommend the doctor for any dental related issue particularly Oral Lichen Planus.
 
I was suffering from Oral Lichen Planus for the last 3 years which became very acute and was finding very difficult to eat even less spicy foods and thought that I would suffer like this during my life time, until I visited Dr Srinivas about a month back.
 
Thankfully I was referred this Dr by my gynecologist during one of my visit.  I am so lucky and extremely happy to meet Dr K Srinivas who is very kind and listened to my sufferings and treated me for Oral Lichen Planus.  It is less than a month now I am taking treatment from him and I am highly grateful and indebted to him for treating me where I find more than 70% improvement and able to eat little spicy food. Before visiting him I had consulted other Doctors who advised and treated but not of much use.
Simplicity and ease of doctor access. ***** ************* experience doctor providing comfortable interaction.
Excellent experience!! The doctor explained the problem clearly and advised the next steps as well.

My mother was diagnosed with Bechets syndrome around eight years back and was under medication. This is a very rare disorder that causes blood vessel inflammation throughout the body. It affects the mouth, Dry eyes, Joint pain. Even having proper food became difficult. Recently the situation was bad and there was severe bleeding from gums and redness in the gum. We approached Dr. Srinivas. He did a detailed investigation of the patient, coordinated with other rheumatologists and started the treatment with proper information to all the family members. Within two days of staring the medication, my mother was able to have light and soft food and within 10 days she had normal food. Post investigation during the first visit itself, doctor gave a Confidence that he will be able to reduce the impact by 90% within one-month time. Currently after one month, the situation is that she is in very good condition, taking proper food as normal. The gum bleeding is completely stopped and gum redness is also gone. I have never seen my mother taking food without any pains / issues in the last 8 years. This doctor is very gifted and am really glad to have approached him for treatment. 
With this experience, I highly recommend Dr. Srinivas for any dental related issues as he is highly capable.

I visited Dr Srinivas for my treatment of Oral Lichen Planus. Prior to his consultation, I visited 3 other doctors. No one gave me a proper explanation as to what happening with me. I use to get painful blisters in my mouth and it was causing difficulty in eating. On my visit to a ENT specialist, who identified that I might be suffering from  Lichen Planus, she suggested me to visit this doctor as he was a specialist in it.

Dr Srinivas, on consultation, spoke to the point. He quickly diagnosed my case. He gave me a thorough review of the potential causes, treatments and prevention measures. He did an oral biopsy to verify the issue and it came out positive for Oral Lichen Planus.  He then suggested a medicine for it along  control measures and changes in dietary habits. Since then I have visible improvement with my case. I would definitely recommend it. Hoping to see more improvements with his help.
I have been consulting Dr Srinivas for many years now. I have built a lot of trust on his ability to cure me and give me appropriate advice. Highly recommended.
